{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"anchor":"Guides","generated":true,"title":"Guides"}],"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],"anchor":"Related","title":"Related"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"article","metadata":{"title":"Running BlueBubbles iMessage Server","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/bluebubbles.app","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is an open-source app that brings","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"iMessage to Android, Windows, and Linux. It requires a macOS server running"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"24\/7 to relay messages. Traditionally, users set this up on a dedicated Mac"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or through a complex VMware-on-Windows process involving OpenCore, QEMU"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"image conversion, Auto-Unlocker patches, and manual VMX editing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.bluebubbles.app\/server\/advanced\/macos-virtualization\/running-a-macos-vm"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular eliminates all of that."}]},{"type":"text","text":" On an Apple Silicon Mac, you run"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"one command and get an isolated macOS VM ready for BlueBubbles — using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s official Virtualization framework, no Hackintosh tools required."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Why-a-VM-instead-of-bare-metal","text":"Why a VM instead of bare metal?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Isolation","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — BlueBubbles needs Full Disk Access to read iMessage’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"chat database. Running it in a VM keeps it sandboxed from your daily Mac.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Snapshots","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — save a working iMessage configuration before macOS"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"updates, roll back if something breaks."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Dedicated environment","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — the VM can run 24\/7 headless while you"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"use your Mac normally."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Two servers","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — run two BlueBubbles instances (e.g., personal +","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"family Apple IDs) on one Mac using Spooktacular’s 2-VM support."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"text":"Quick Start","anchor":"Quick-Start","type":"heading"},{"level":3,"text":"1. Create a VM","anchor":"1-Create-a-VM","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook create bluebubbles --from-ipsw latest \\","    --cpu 4 --memory 4 --disk 32 \\","    --network nat \\","    --user-data .\/setup-bluebubbles.sh \\","    --provision disk-inject"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"BlueBubbles is lightweight — 4 CPU cores and 4 GB RAM is plenty."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"2. The setup script","anchor":"2-The-setup-script"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"setup-bluebubbles.sh"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["#!\/bin\/bash","# setup-bluebubbles.sh — installs BlueBubbles server in a macOS VM","","set -euo pipefail","","# Install Homebrew","\/bin\/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/Homebrew\/install\/HEAD\/install.sh)\"","eval \"$(\/opt\/homebrew\/bin\/brew shellenv)\"","","# Install BlueBubbles server","brew install --cask bluebubbles-server","","# Enable Screen Sharing for remote management","sudo \/System\/Library\/CoreServices\/RemoteManagement\/ARDAgent.app\/Contents\/Resources\/kickstart \\","    -activate -configure -access -on -restart -agent -privs -all","","echo \"BlueBubbles server installed.\"","echo \"Connect via VNC to complete Apple ID sign-in and BlueBubbles setup.\""]},{"text":"3. Start and configure","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"3-Start-and-configure"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook start bluebubbles"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The VM opens with a display window. Complete these one-time steps:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Sign in to your Apple ID","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — required for iMessage"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Open Messages.app","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — verify iMessage activates","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Launch BlueBubbles Server"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — configure your connection","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(Firebase, Cloudflare tunnel, or Tailscale)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Grant Full Disk Access","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — System Settings → Privacy &"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Security → Full Disk Access → add BlueBubbles"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"4. Run headless 24\/7","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"4-Run-headless-247"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once configured, restart headless:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook stop bluebubbles","spook start bluebubbles --headless"],"syntax":"bash"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The BlueBubbles server runs in the background. Access it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"remotely via VNC if you need to make changes:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook ip bluebubbles","# Connect via Screen Sharing to the reported IP"],"syntax":"bash"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Two-BlueBubbles-Instances","type":"heading","text":"Two BlueBubbles Instances"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Run two iMessage servers on one Mac — one for each Apple ID:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook create bb-personal --from-ipsw latest --cpu 4 --memory 4","spook create bb-family --from-ipsw latest --cpu 4 --memory 4","","# Or clone from a configured base:","spook create bb-personal --from-ipsw latest --user-data .\/setup-bluebubbles.sh","# Configure Apple ID #1...","spook stop bb-personal","","spook clone bb-personal bb-family","# Start bb-family and sign in with Apple ID #2","spook start bb-family","# Configure Apple ID #2...","","# Run both headless","spook start bb-personal --headless","spook start bb-family --headless"],"syntax":"bash"},{"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Each VM gets a unique ","type":"text"},{"code":"VZMacMachineIdentifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"iMessage activation is per-machine-identifier. Cloning creates","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a new identity, so you must re-activate iMessage on the clone.","type":"text"}]}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Comparison-Spooktacular-vs-VMware-on-Windows","type":"heading","text":"Comparison: Spooktacular vs VMware-on-Windows"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.bluebubbles.app\/server\/advanced\/macos-virtualization\/running-a-macos-vm\/deploying-macos-in-vmware-on-windows-full-guide","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requires 20+ steps including BIOS configuration, Python\/QEMU","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"installation, OpenCore recovery download, DMG-to-VMDK conversion,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Auto-Unlocker patching, VMX file editing, and Clover Configurator","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for iServices. It runs macOS on non-Apple hardware (unsupported","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by Apple, may violate the EULA).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"VMware on Windows","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Steps to working VM"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"20+ manual steps"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"1 command","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS installation"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OpenCore + Recovery","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s official IPSW"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Hardware","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any x86 PC"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon Mac"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple EULA","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Violates (non-Apple HW)","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Compliant","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iMessage activation","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Requires fake serial numbers"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Works natively"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Performance"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Emulated, slow"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Near-native (VirtIO)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"GPU acceleration","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Metal via VZ framework","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Maintenance"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Manual patching per update","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook create --from-ipsw latest"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Snapshots","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"VMware snapshots","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook snapshot"},{"type":"text","text":" (APFS)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"24\/7 headless","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Complex configuration","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start --headless"}]}]]]},{"anchor":"iCloud-and-iMessage-in-VMs","text":"iCloud and iMessage in VMs","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As of macOS 15 (Sequoia), Apple officially supports iCloud sign-in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"inside macOS VMs created with the Virtualization framework. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"means iMessage activation works natively — no fake serial numbers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or Clover Configurator needed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iCloud support requires macOS 15+ on both the host and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the guest. Earlier macOS versions may have issues with iMessage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"activation in VMs. See Apple’s documentation:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/virtualization\/using-icloud-with-macos-virtual-machines"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Networking for BlueBubbles","anchor":"Networking-for-BlueBubbles"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"BlueBubbles needs outbound internet access to reach Firebase\/Cloudflare."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"NAT n